  buttonSpacingY: 86
  hubTitle: VR Stress Response Trainer
  hubConnectionStatusDemo: 'Smartwatch: Not connected (simulated HR/HRV)

    Android
    gateway: Not in use'
  introNarrationText: "In recent years, many of us have experienced stress and pressure
    due to emergency situations and war.\n\nThis training experience is designed
    to help improve your ability to function under stress.\n\nPlease connect your
    smartwatch. \n\nIn each simulation, your physiological response is measured and
    at the end you receive practical recommendations for next time."
  introParagraph1: In recent years, many of us have experienced stress and pressure
    due to emergency situations and war.
  introParagraph2: This training experience is designed to help improve your ability
    to function under stress.
  introParagraph3: Please connect your smartwatch.
  introParagraph4: In each simulation, your physiological response is measured and
    at the end you receive practical recommendations for next time.
  introParagraph1Start: 0
  introParagraph2Start: 6
  introParagraph3Start: 10
  introParagraph4Start: 13.5
  calibrationInstruction: "Stand still and relax. \nWe are calibrating your heart-rate
    metrics.\nNo alarm will play during this step."
  missionBriefingBody: "Simulation 1 - Emergency preparedness\n\nA loud continuous
    siren will start when the mission begins.\n\nCollect three essential items inside
    the home:\n\u2022 Watet Bottle\n\u2022 Flash Light\n\u2022 Radio\nAfter collecting
    all 3 items, run to the Mamad (shelter) outside.\n\nWhen you are ready, press
    Start mission."
  sim2BriefingBody: "Simulation 2 \u2013 First Aid Under Pressure\n\nYou are in an
    outdoor courtyard while the alarm is active.\nYour mission is to treat the casualty.\n\nHow
    to complete treatment:\n1) Approach the casualty and press E to start.\n2) Follow
    the on-screen steps.\n3) Press the required keys in order (1 \u2192 2 \u2192
    3) until treatment is complete.\n\nStay calm, breathe slowly, and focus on one
    step at a time.\n\nPress Start Simulation 2 when you are ready."
  calibrationDurationSeconds: 10
  runSimulation2InSameScene: 1
  simulation2SceneIndex: 1
